    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1554½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-04">4 <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >March</hi>, 1915</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The green paper despatch
                    attached hereto<note n="47" xml:id="d237fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> seems to me abrupt in expression and
                    also a bit difficult to interpret as it stands. I therefore beg that, in its
                    stead, you will send to Ambassador Page at London Mr. Lansing’s letter to you
                    (also attached),<note n="47a" xml:id="d237fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_270">p. 270</ref>.</note> as I
                    have taken the liberty of altering it.<note n="48" xml:id="d237fn3">This was
                        done; for the telegram as sent, see <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_132">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                        132</ref>.</note> It is both lucid and conveys the matter in just the right
                    tone of inquiry.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
